snippet.textDisplay: Unrelated to this video, but since it's the most recent- I'm new to your channel and you've already helped me in my life. It may seem superficial but is not-- I've always been a musician and gone to concerts, but I was with my ex for 10 years, my whole adult life, and then not anymore. I've been single for 2 years and not been able to make myself go to a concert alone, have missed my most favorite bands multiple times. I'm too anxious, there's the walking long distances in the dark on city streets late at night, etc. You talked in multiple videos about making yourself do things that made you uncomfortable- so I did it, I bought my just one concert ticket, and I'm just going to do it, and I even got two days off work for it so I can't back out or have any excuses. Something about you talking about how you haven't mastered these life things makes me feel like we can try together.

snippet.textDisplay:
I'm confused about people saying these are expensive. Aren't Colourpop shadows $5 each? I know their palletes are cheaper, but those are mini shadows. The Mug singles have WAY more product in them and are customizable.

I guess if you want all 56 that's an investment, but unless you're a makeup artist or trying to build a collection, I don't think it's intended that you buy the mega palletes. The whole point of the matrix system is to make your perfect everyday pallete and use every shade until it's gone.

Maybe I'm totally missing something. Can someone explain?
